<title>An explanation about the ionic square lattice</title>
<border>Raised Bevel</border>
<hint_text>&lt;html&gt; When materials crystalize, their internal energy is lowered. But &lt;br&gt; this does not necessarily result in closed-packness. When the &lt;br&gt; number of molecules with positive charges and the number of atoms &lt;br&gt; with negative charges are equal (a requirement of neutrality), &lt;br&gt; ionic crystal lattices favor alternate alignment of positive and &lt;br&gt; negative charges on the vertices, which is obvious on a square &lt;br&gt; lattice but not on a hexganoal lattice.&lt;/html&gt;</hint_text>
